    public class ValueFactoryParser<V,C extends V,ABT,A extends C,JBT,J extends C,B extends V,M extends V,N extends V,S extends V>
extends Parser
    A JSON→URL text parser bound to a ValueFactory.

    An instance of this class may be used to parse JSON→URL text and instantiate JVM heap Objects. The interface allows you to control the types and values of the Objects. This is really just a convenience wrapper around Parser. It accepts a ValueFactory in the constructor and uses it whenever a ValueFactory is called for.

    Normally this class isn't used by directly but rather it's subclassed with specific types and an instance of ValueFactory.
